cyan【🩵】resident weeb・rap nerd 2024-12-17 9:18 AM
So we made coffee paintings for contemporary arts, and i was supposed to do an alleyway in sweden but since i started on a new blank paper and overslept, i instead decided to settle for a blåhaj. This medium is so hard to get right (at least for me) because it takes too long to dry (not in a good way) and I can't get the coffee dark enough on paper that doesn't mix with the lighter shaded parts. I rushed this in one hour because today is the deadline and of course, the coffee flowed along the paper on the way to school and ruined the shape. It still looks like a shonk i guess so i just rolled with it but then my classmate did a RIDICULOUSLY GOOD PAINTING OF AN EYE and you know what he said? "It sucks lol" Honestly it felt like a slap to the face as someone who isn't good at art but loves art more than anything and I'll admit i sometimes say my art looks bad but i try to at least keep it to myself because imagine doing a piece that impressive and then call it ass in front of someone who clearly has a more ass work
9:19 AM
And my allergies are acting up rn so it makes my body more depressed
9:20 AM
If only I didn't overslept last night, the coffee would've dried better...
